Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Beijing, March 31 (XINHUA) -- French Prime Minister 
Edouard Balladur will pay an official visit to China from April 
7 to 10 as guest of Premier Li Peng, announced a Foreign 
Ministry spokesman here today. 
  Speaking at weekly press conference, the spokesman said that 
Balladur's China tour is "an important political visit." 
  "It will give major impetus to the further development of 
the 
bilateral ties between China and France, including economic and 
trade relations," he said. 
  Maintaining good political relations will provide a solid 
foundation and favorable conditions for the development of 
mutually beneficial economic and trade relations between the two 
countries, he said. 

